0 -14 Td
(This policy defines how fictional project teams store, review, redact, publish, and retire) Tj
0 -14 Td
(documents that may be used in a public-facing AI demonstration environment. Its purpose is to) Tj
0 -14 Td
(prevent accidental inclusion of private, identifying, or proprietary material while preserving) Tj
0 -14 Td
(enough structure for realistic testing.) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(DEFINITIONS) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Synthetic document: a file created entirely for demonstration or testing and not derived) Tj
0 -14 Td
(from private operational material.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Redacted document: a file whose sensitive content has been replaced with safe placeholders) Tj
0 -14 Td
(and reviewed for residual identifiers in text, metadata, and images.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Prohibited source: any real internal, customer, employee, vendor, or security-sensitive) Tj
0 -14 Td
(content that is not approved for unrestricted public release.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Derived artifact: OCR output, extracted text, embeddings, screenshots, logs, or caches) Tj
0 -14 Td
(produced from a prohibited source.) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(REQUIREMENTS) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Keep public repository sample data limited to synthetic or fully redacted content that a) Tj
0 -14 Td
(third party could inspect without restriction.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Store working drafts containing unresolved redactions only in a local excluded path until) Tj
0 -14 Td
(review is complete.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Review filenames, embedded metadata, document properties, and visible page content before) Tj
0 -14 Td
(any sample file is committed.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Retain synthetic demonstration documents as long as they support evaluation, examples, or) Tj
0 -14 Td
(user-interface testing, provided they remain current with the project scope.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Delete or replace sample documents that reference outdated controls, deprecated) Tj
0 -14 Td
(architectures, or naming patterns likely to confuse future reviewers.) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(PROHIBITED PRACTICES) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Do not commit real manuals, internal screenshots, vendor exports, customer notes, OCR output) Tj
0 -14 Td
(from private files, or debug logs derived from private materials.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Do not rely on simple name replacement if the surrounding details still reveal a real site,) Tj
